<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="536" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,510,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1482,1507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="536">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name is the Latin word “dilatata” meaning expanded. It refers to the ventrally expanded margin of the style blade.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,510,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,1554,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="536">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli, 2019" authorityName="Domahovski &amp; Cavichioli" authorityYear="2019" box="[288,486,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acusana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilatata" status="sp. nov.">
